A: You can use a boolean variable to check if the ProgressDialog is showing or not.
boolean isProgressDialogShowing = false;

Then, in your prepareViews method, you can set this variable to true when the ProgressDialog is shown and to false when it is dismissed.
case CONNECTING_DIALOG:
    if(state == true){
        if(!isProgressDialogShowing){
            progressDialog = ProgressDialog.show(MainActivity.this, "", "Connecting", true);
            isProgressDialogShowing = true;
        }
    } else{
        if(isProgressDialogShowing && progressDialog != null){
            progressDialog.dismiss();
            isProgressDialogShowing = false;
        }
    }
    break;

This way, you can prevent the ProgressDialog from being dismissed
